  "text": "# SmartSaver Account FAQ  \n## Account Basics  \n**Q: What is the SmartSaver Account?**\nA: It's an easy-access savings account that earns variable interest. You can deposit and withdraw money anytime with no penalties or waiting periods. It's designed for customers who want a flexible savings account with competitive interest rates.  \n**Q: Who can open a SmartSaver Account?**\nA: Anyone who is:\n- At least 18 years old\n- A UK resident\n- Able to provide UK Passport or Driving License\n- Able to provide proof of address  \n**Q: Is there a minimum balance requirement?**\nA: No. You can open an account with just £1.00. There's no minimum balance to keep the account open.  \n**Q: How do I open a SmartSaver Account?**\nA: You can open an account:\n- **Online:** Visit www.firstuk.bank and click \"Open Account\"\n- **In Branch:** Visit any FirstUK Bank branch\n- **By Post:** Call 0800-555-2265 to request postal application pack  \n**Q: How long does it take to open an account?**\nA:\n- Online/Branch: 1–2 business days\n- Postal: 5–7 business days  \n---",
